# Full Stack Cloud-Native Application

## Overview
A containerized full-stack web application deployed on Kubernetes clusters (AWS EKS / GCP GKE) with CI/CD pipelines and cloud-native storage. Demonstrates end-to-end DevOps and cloud integration.

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: React.js
- Backend: Node.js / Express
- Database: PostgreSQL / Cloud SQL
- Containerization: Docker, Helm
- Kubernetes (EKS/GKE)
- Terraform (IaC)
- CI/CD: GitHub Actions
- Storage: AWS S3 / GCP Cloud Storage

## Features
- Multi-service containerized architecture
- Automated CI/CD pipelines
- Cloud-native storage for static assets
- Rolling updates and zero downtime deployment
- Infrastructure as Code using Terraform

## Architecture Diagram
![Architecture Diagram](./docs/architecture.png)

## Setup Instructions
1. Clone the repo
2. Setup frontend and backend:
   ```bash
   cd frontend
   npm install
   npm run build
   cd ../backend
   npm install
   npm start
